main event: An observer spotted several unusual objects in the sky while in visual flight near Eglin AFB, Florida, on April 12, 1967.
interesting points: The objects were moving with a great deal of speed,The observer initially thought the objects were falling stars,They were ultimately determined to be aircraft after investigation,The observer was a civilian inspector at Eglin AFB with 15 years of experience,The objects appeared to vanish one by one after being visible for 5 to 10 seconds.
sighted object: several unusual objects in the sky
witness description: Patrick J., a civilian, age 19, with 15 years of experience at Eglin AFB, and Mr. Froeman, known as an honest person.
